                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <hi rend=\"underline\">\n                                                  <placeName>Macon Geo.</placeName>\n                                                  <date>March 19<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi>/49</date>\n                                        </hi>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>Rev Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I trust <sic>ze</sic> object of my letter will be\n                                        a<lb/> sufficient excuse for <sic>ze</sic> liberty I take in\n                                        address<lb/>-ing you. In preparing a paper for\n                                        publication<lb/> on <add>the?</add> “Original Units of\n                                                  <sic>ze</sic> American Race,” I have met<lb/>\n                                        <sic>ze</sic> following objection advanced in a review of\n                                                  <persName>Dr<lb/> Pritchard's</persName> work on\n                                                  “<sic>ze</sic> natural History of Man”—<lb/>\n                                        <sic>Ze</sic> reviewer says, “According to <sic>ze</sic>\n                                        Mosaic account <del>of</del><lb/> as generally interpreted\n                                        it was necessary, for <sic>ze</sic><lb/> continuance of\n                                                  <sic>ze</sic> human race, that\n                                                  <persName>Adam's</persName> sons<lb/> should\n                                        cohabit with their sisters. But that was<lb/> incest,\n                                        against which <sic>ze</sic> punishment of death was<lb/>\n                                        afterwards (!) proclaimed by <persName>Moses</persName>\n                                        himself, as I<lb/> express command of <sic>ze</sic> Deity”\n                                        It is very evident that<lb/>\n                                        <sic>ze</sic> author (<persName>Dr Caldwell</persName>) has\n                                        here advanced a weak<lb/> &amp; absurd proposition: for that\n                                        which was unlaw<lb/>-ful after <persName>Moses</persName>\n                                        had received <sic>ze</sic> command-<lb/>-ments was certainly\n                                        lawful previous to that<lb/> event. If members of\n                                                  <sic>ze</sic> same family did, as<lb/> it is\n                                        useless to deny, cohabit, they received <add>?</add><lb/>\n                                        Creator's blessing &amp; command to multiply &amp;\n                                        replen-<lb/>-ish <sic>ze</sic> Earth. So with\n                                                  <persName>Noah</persName>. So with Sat.<lb/> But\n                                        it is useless for me appeal to <sic>ze</sic> instances<lb/>\n                                        of proof in <sic>ze</sic> scripture. They will at once<lb/>\n                                        suggest themselves to <hi rend=\"underline\">your</hi> mind.\n                                        What I desire<lb/> is a more definite knowledge of\n                                                  <sic>ze</sic> view taken</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3g15tt46/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
